  "text": "The volume of water drawn into milk by osmotic forces is related to lactose synthesis and therefore, a-LA is a deciding factor in the ultimate milk volume. [CITATION_1] used transgenic gilts expressing bovine a-LA in their milk to study whether the presence of the transgene influences lactation. They reported that lactose concentrations and milk production increased in the experimental group and that the piglets reared on the transgenic animals exhibited enhanced growth rates.",
